on these points:<br>
<br>
Point 3).   One word.. or rather spell.  Concussion.  Any wizard who doesn't have it is a fool.  Very nice to have if you've got to chose between a +3 mana regen Rune and the BST +(7-9?) mana regen spell.<br>
<br>
Point 4).  Bazaar isn't the only place to look for spells.  I've found the high-end guilds can be very sympathetic to wizards.. especially if you've helped them in the past with some of their epics.  (Particularly Cleric Epics..)<br>
<br>
Point 5).  Oh, they can bang alright.. but everything I've heard about FoT aside from it being a bolt, is that the aggro from that spell alone makes it a nightmare for any mage to use.  Add to that, Druids and Mages rarely select evocation as a speciality, making their spells that much more mana hogs.  They may be able to burn better than us for a time.. but not ALL the time.<br>
<br>
Point 6).  So.. you forsee this as a bad thing?  At lvl 62, its rather nice not to have consant streams of tells asking for TLs.  Plus, I like the added fact, that I don't get asked to go hunt some lazy LFG person.<br>
<br>
Point 7).  Okay, you (and anyone who agrees with you) are so far off on this point.  You have not spent enough time in the PoP dungeon crawls of PoD and PoI.  Most groups I know of, unless they aren't going very far from zin, will take a gater.  This allows them to continue exp'ing until the point when the group has to change hands or break up.  Also an evac'ing group has a much improved turn-around time, which can be nice if you just cleared your way to that sweet spot.  Basic Dungeon 101, man, basic Dungeon 101 on speed.<br>
<br>
Point 9).  Seems to me all the classes have this problem.<br>
<br>
Point 10).  Get SCF and SCFM.  Now that I crit alot, I find that peeps remember me.. and thus I get more groups.  SCM helps out as well. <p>Master Orakkus Mu'Hadeeb<br>
