One point you make I'd like to expand on is:<br>
&quot;6) decline in usefulness of Translocates and Ports due to PoK and Nexus portals<br>
This decreases my enjoyment by... eliminating the need for a major skill upon which my class is built. I have a whole spellbook filled with TLs and gates whose value was reduced dramatically the second PoP and SoL hit the shelves. Ease of transportation was a MAJOR reason I chose to be a Wizard. If I were to start again today, it wouldn't even be a consideration. I feel duped.&quot;<br>
<br>
I've been thinking about this quite a bit lately. Why you ask? Well it kind of ties in to my first little ramble. I'm L57 and have amassed not a bad, guess that's relative, amount of coin - around 60K. I've gotten all my spells thru 59 and all the vendor sold 60 ones. I've been in the bazaar looking at getting some of the 60 drop ones and when I see prices in the 20-50K range I think &quot;good lord I'll never be able to buy them let alone the 61+&quot;. I've been thinking about what it is we as Wizzys can do for money.<br>
<br>
Chanters routinely sit in Nexus and make 100pp per head for casting KEI. Wouldn't take too long, and their sure seems like enough customers, for a Chanter to afford those 20K spells.  Clerics, at least on my server, have taken up regular residence in GY of the planes and make 50-100pp or higher per rez. Mages summon a ton of focus items and sell them pretty fast and for anywhere from 10-50pp depending on the item (again at least on my server). What about Wizzys, and for that matter melees, Necs, &amp; Druids these days. What can we do to make cash?  Well it used to be ports but I'm finding more and more either people don't need them or they aren't offering much for them (we won't even talk about the folks that want a port and offer 3pp saying &quot;I could just use the PoP portals but I'm lazy).<br>
<br>
So I guess your #6 point also brings out the issue with we and Druids making good amounts by porting anymore  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   This isn't class envy either. I just wonder who the geniuses are in VI/SoE that don't see the large discrepencies of having some classes with an almost innate ability to make cash quickly and the rest of the classes. /shrug just my whacky mind working overtime <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
