<br>
in no way is it the same and to think so is idiotic. first off, again, were talking about trash mobs, which dont require the tactics that boss mobs do, generally. secondly, on these mobs, yes, rogs stay opposite the MT and hit their hotkeys when they pop. thirdly, have you ever played a wizard? to achieve max DPS, you have to pick what spells to use and when to use them (always better to lead with a big nuke after you know the general agro limits, lead with a rain if resists and lack of adds allow it), you need to know to use concussion only when its needed based on time and raid agro (or you are wasting much DPS), and probably most importantly, you need to know your refresh time for all your spells and time the tflux/recast to as soon as possible without getting a 'didnt not refresh' message. you should always be casting something, chaining your spells as fast as possible, and you should never gain agro. one nuke can easily make the difference on exp or not, particularly if youre the only main damage dealer in your group.<br>
<br>
i just KSed a 30 person ixi raid when the cleric was purposely put in 'the exp group'. it died so fast i only had time for 4 spells. my 4 spells outdamaged a rog, 62 wiz, epic mage, monk and the MT.<br>
<br>
learn to operate at the best of your abilities.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
&quot;2) Wizards have often been heard to complain that their sustainable DPS is too low to make them desirable in exp groups. Yet you are implying that, if you are on the ball, you outdamage a rogue, possibly even 2 of them. So are you saying you would think it balanced if wizards did the same sustained DPS as a rogue AND could outdamage them 2 to 1 when desired?&quot;<br>
