No one is intended to go solo trakanon, its still useful and every boss we hit we have people manaburning.<br>
<br>
2) Loss of crits on Manaburn<br>
Dunno why this was removed, I didn't/don't have a problem with manaburn crits<br>
<br>
3) Inability of epic buff to stack with BST mana regen spells<br>
Annoying I am sure, no argument here<br>
<br>
4) Inability to obtain Sunstrike, GSS, EER as well as other less desirable but useful high-end spells<br>
People get Sunstrike and EER, it may be hard for the very casual player but it is possible even if frustrating.  GSS is the only one I dont see becoming commonplace for 6 months or more.  THO drops EER and hes not all that anymore.<br>
<br>
5) Relative availability of comparable Druid nukes (Moonfire) and Mage nukes (FoT)<br>
Its all about the ratio, 95%+ of mages are conj spec'd and the FoT is a bolt...miss one and your ratio/efficency goes right out the window.  I can speak to the druid one.<br>
<br>
6) Decline in usefulness of Translocates and Ports due to PoK and Nexus portals<br>
Well this may be true, and I am not saying it is, anything that makes transportation availible to the masses is a good thing imo.  I still see people asking for TL/Ports all the time instead of waiting 15 min or so on nexus or running around looking for the right pedestal.  Its all about convienence, wiz/druid ports will always be more convienent assuming there is one near you.  But what happens to that non-porter if they are not there?  Well for the longest time they were stuck walking and taking boats.<br>
<br>
7) Decline in usefulness of Evacs in PoP due to graveyards<br>
How so...there is a zone in evac, Succor or something? (not a porting class sorry)  I havent seen anyone picked for a group specifically to be an evac since kunark era.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Nerf to quadding due to new aggro (such as in CS)<br>
I cannot comment, I could never quad =P<br>
<br>
9) Raid exp system eliminating extra Wizard exp on raids<br>
WTF lol.  That is a pure 100% selfish whine right there.  You think the other 50 people on that raid are there so you can get &quot;extra Wizard xp&quot;?<br>
<br>
10) Inability to find a role in traditional exp groups<br>
Well while I can sympathize with your case, all pure damage classes are having group issues atm.  You could also start your own or get a group of friends/guildmates to xp with regularly. <p><hr>
